definition.value: Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + (R)-pantoate + beta-alanine -eq- AMP + diphosphate + (R)-pantothenate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-pantothenate + H(2)O -eq- (R)-pantoate + beta-alanine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + pantothenate -eq- ADP + D-4'-phosphopantothenate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + pantetheine 4'-phosphate -eq- 3'-dephospho-CoA + diphosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  acetyl-CoA + peptide -eq- CoA + N-alpha-acetylpeptide. This reaction is the acetylation of the N-terminal amino acid residue of a peptide or protein.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptide L-aspartate + 2-oxoglutarate + O2 -eq- peptide 3-hydroxy-L-aspartate + succinate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  peptidylamidoglycolate -eq- peptidyl amide + glyoxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  donor + hydrogen peroxide -eq- oxidized donor + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2 glutathione + hydrogen peroxide -eq- oxidized glutathione + 2 H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + phenylethanolamine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + N-methylphenylethanolamine.

Catalysis of the reaction -  adenosine 3',5'-diphosphate + H(+) + sulfite + thioredoxin disulfide -eq- 3'-phospho-5'-adenylyl sulfate + thioredoxin. Thioredoxin disulfide is the oxidized form of thioredoxin -  3'-phosphoadenosine 5'-phosphosulfate is also known as PAPS.
Catalysis of the reaction -  CTP + phosphatidate -eq- diphosphate + CDP-diacylglycerol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphatidylcholine + a sterol -eq- a sterol ester + 1-acylglycerophosphocholine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  S-adenosyl-L-methionine + phosphatidylethanolamine -eq- S-adenosyl-L-homocysteine + H(+) + phosphatidyl-N-methylethanolamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  H(+) + phosphatidyl-L-serine -eq- CO(2) + phosphatidylethanolamine.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-acetyl-alpha-D-glucosamine 1-phosphate -eq- N-acetyl-D-glucosamine 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  source of phosphate + oxaloacetate -eq- phosphoenolpyruvate + CO2 + other reaction products.
Catalysis of the reaction -  ATP + oxaloacetate -eq- ADP + CO(2) + H(+) + phosphoenolpyruvate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  GTP + oxaloacetate -eq- GDP + phosphoenolpyruvate + CO2.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate -eq- alpha-D-glucose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  alpha-D-mannose 1-phosphate -eq- D-mannose 6-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  6-phospho-D-gluconate + NADP+ -eq- D-ribulose 5-phosphate + CO2 + NADPH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phosphoglycerate + NAD+ -eq- 3-phosphohydroxypyruvate + NADH + H+.
Catalysis of the reaction -  3-phospho-D-glycerate + ATP -eq- 3-phospho-D-glyceroyl phosphate + ADP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phospho-D-glycerate -eq- 3-phospho-D-glycerate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of a glycerophospholipid.
Catalysis of the reaction -  glycoprotein phosphatidylinositol + H2O -eq- phosphatidate + glycoprotein inositol.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-lysophosphatidylcholine + H2O -eq- glycerophosphocholine + a carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  phosphatidylcholine + H2O -eq- 1-acylglycerophosphocholine + a carboxylate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a phospholipid + H2O -eq- 1,2-diacylglycerol + a phosphatidate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  a phosphatidylcholine + H2O -eq- choline + a phosphatidate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  (R)-5-phosphomevalonate + ATP -eq- (R)-5-diphosphomevalonate + ADP + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  CTP + (R)-4'-phosphopantothenate + L-cysteine -eq- CMP + diphosphate + (R)-4'-phosphopantothenoyl-L-cysteine. Cysteine can be replaced by some of its derivatives.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-[(R)-4-phosphonatopantothenoyl]-L-cysteinate + H(+) -eq- CO(2) + pantetheine 4'-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-phospho-D-glycerate -eq- phosphoenolpyruvate + H2O.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-(5-phosphonatoribosyl)-5'-AMP + H(2)O -eq- 1-(5-phosphoribosyl)-5-[(5-phosphoribosylamino)methylideneamino]imidazole-4-carboxamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)-ATP + H(2)O -eq- 1-(5-phosphonatoribosyl)-5'-AMP + diphosphate + H(+).
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-phospho-D-ribosylamine + ATP + glycine -eq- N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxylate + 2 H(+) -eq- 5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole + CO(2).

Catalysis of the reaction -  5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxylate + L-aspartate + ATP -eq- (2S)-2-[5-amino-1-(5-phospho-beta-D-ribosyl)imidazole-4-carboxamido]succinate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  N-(5-phospho-beta-D-ribosyl)anthranilate -eq- 1-(2-carboxyphenylamino)-1-deoxy-D-ribulose 5-phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  2-(formamido)-N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)acetamidine + ATP -eq- 5-amino-1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)imidazole + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.

Catalysis of the reaction -  N(2)-formyl-N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide + L-glutamine + ATP + H(2)O -eq- 2-(formamido)-N(1)-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)acetamidine + L-glutamate + ADP + 2 H(+) + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  10-formyltetrahydrofolate + 5'-phosphoribosyl-5-amino-4-imidazolecarboxamide -eq- tetrahydrofolate + 5'-phosphoribosyl-5-formamido-4-imidazolecarboxamide.
Catalysis of the reaction -  10-formyltetrahydrofolate + N1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide -eq- tetrahydrofolate + N2-formyl-N1-(5-phospho-D-ribosyl)glycinamide.

Catalysis of the reaction -  1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n) + phosphate -eq- 1,4-alpha-D-glucosyl(n-1) + alpha-D-glucose 1-phosphate. The name should be qualified in each instance by adding the name of the natural substrate, e.g. maltodextrin phosphorylase, starch phosphorylase, glycogen phosphorylase.
Catalysis of the reaction -  L(or D)-O-phosphoserine + H2O -eq- L(or D)-serine + phosphate.
Catalysis of the reaction -  O-phospho-L-serine + 2-oxoglutarate -eq- 3-phosphonooxypyruvate + L-glutamate.
Catalysis of the hydrolysis of poly(ADP-ribose) at glycosidic (1''-2') linkage of ribose-ribose bond to produce free ADP-ribose.
Catalysis of the random hydrolysis of (1--gt-4)-alpha-D-galactosiduronic linkages in pectate and other galacturonans.
